Interface IService

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IConversion, IDataSourceService, IModelInterpreter, IQueryProcessor, ISimulator
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AConversion, AExternalProcessNeuronalSimulator, AExternalProcessSimulator, AModelInterpreter, AService, ASimulator, ColladaModelInterpreterService, JNeuroMLSimulatorService, LEMSConversionService, LEMSModelInterpreterService, LEMSSimulatorService, NetPyNENSGSimulatorService, NetPyNESimulatorService, NeuroMLModelInterpreterService, NeuronNSGSimulatorService, NeuronSimulatorService, NSGSimulatorService, NWBModelInterpreterService, ObjModelInterpreterService, SWCModelInterpreterService, TestConversion, TestConversion2, TestModelInterpreter, TestModelInterpreter2, TestModelInterpreterService, TestSimulator, TestSimulator2, TestSimulatorService

    public interface IService
    This interface defines the common functionalities to be implemented by every service. It provides the ability to register a service in the Service Registry and the ability to selectively implement different features.
    Author:
    Adrian Quintana (adrian.perez@ucl.ac.uk), matteocantarelli
